import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.hist(data['precipitation'], bins=30, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'], label='Max Temperature')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['temp_min'], label='Min Temperature')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature (°C)')
    ax.set_title('How does temperature vary over time?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['wind', 'temp_max']]
    plt.scatter(data['wind'], data['temp_max'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Wind')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind and temperature?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['weather'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'green', 'grey', 'orange', 'red'])
    plt.title('What is the most common type of weather in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Type')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.legend()
    plt.axhline(y=data['weather'].value_counts().max(), color='black', linestyle='--', label='Max Frequency: {:.2f}'.format(data['weather'].value_counts().max()))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
